text.section:
A person may not sell or otherwise provide bichloride of mercury in a tablet that contains more than one-tenth of a grain of bichloride of mercury unless the tablet:
Has the word "Poison" impressed or embossed on it;
Is triangular, diamond, square, oblong, or irregular in shape;
Is blue, green, or purple in color; and
Is contained in a bottle that has the word "Poison" blown in one side of the bottle and a label on the opposite side that bears the word "Poison" in conspicuous letters.
